  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity study was conducted varying Young's modulus ±10% and friction coefficient across three levels; results confirmed that QoI predictions shift by less than 3%, supporting robustness of the nominal parameter set. This UQ screening is documented in the technical report but is not linked as a structured SensitivityAnalysis node.",
