      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model physics (linear-elastic titanium alloy, frictional contact at screw-rod interface, rigid crosslinks) justified by literature and preliminary analyses; simplifying assumptions documented.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as linear-elastic (E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) consistent with sub-yield loading regime confirmed by strain gauge data. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) at screw-rod interface selected from tribology literature for dry Ti-Ti contact. Bone analog (UHMWPE blocks) modeled as linear-elastic (E=1.0 GPa). Geometric simplifications (filleted screw roots omitted) assessed via local stress sensitivity; effect on global QoIs <0.5%. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from MMPDS and confirmed by coupon testing; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus confirmed by dog-bone coupon tensile testing (n=5; mean 113.8 GPa, CV 0.6%). UHMWPE block modulus from manufacturer datasheet cross-checked against compression coupon testing (n=3; mean 1.02 GPa). Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements of production hardware; dimensional tolerances ±0.02 mm. Nominal input parameter set used for all 11 production runs. A screening sensitivity study (Young's modulus ±10%, friction coefficient 0.15/0.20/0.25) confirmed QoI shifts <3%, supporting adequacy of the nominal parameter selection. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
