      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two loading rates and two construct configurations to assess boundary condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under ASTM F1717 standardized protocol: single loading rate (5 mm/min), single construct configuration (two-level). Only one test condition evaluated; protocol did not include variation in loading rate or construct configuration. This factor does not meet the required Gradation 3. Shortfall documented as an accepted limitation given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard and the COU is specifically defined for this protocol. Required Gradation 3; achieved Gradation 2.",
