      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission endpoints and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs are mechanistically linked to clinical failure modes (fatigue crack initiation, construct loosening). Required Gradation 3 achieved."
