    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 standardized protocol, and regulatory guidance does not require loading rate variation for this submission type. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval <1.96; percent difference <10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in the non-cannulated pedicle screw 510(k) submission.",
